= '''Computing that is conscious of its environmental impact''', resulting in efforts for 
reducing resources required for computing: Reduced power, reduced heating, sleeping and suspending processors and processes.

Concept proposed by Martien van Steenbergen at http://wiki.aardrock.com/Conscious_Computing


=Examples=

From Martien at
http://martien.aardrock.com/2007/07/01/conscious-computing/ :

# [http://arstechnica.com/articles/paedia/cpu/power-plays.ars Power Plays]: How power consumption will shape the future of computing on how Intel is using smart self-organizing principles on chip-level to maximize the performance/power ratio in favour of green or conscious computing.
# Sun’s Jonathan Schwartz on [http://blogs.sun.com/jonathan/entry/size_matters Switching Subjects] to drastically simplify cabling and reducing power and cooling requirements in massive data centers in their Project Magnum and Constellation System.

